{"title_page": "Social Income", "text_new": "{{Infobox organization\n| name = Social Income\n| logo = Social Income Logo.svg\n| logo_size = 250px\n| type = Alleviating [[poverty]] through [[cash transfers]]\n| founded_date = {{Start date and age|2019}}\n| status = Non-Profit Association \n| registration_id = CHE-289.611.695\n| homepage = {{URL|socialincome.org}}\n| location_city = [[Zurich]]\n| area_served = [[Sierra Leone]]\n}}\n\n'''Social Income''' is a [[non-profit organization|nonprofit organization]] operating in West Africa that helps people living in [[poverty]] by making [[unconditional cash transfer]]s to them via mobile phone. Currently Social Income transfers funds to people in need in [[Sierra Leone]].\n\n== History ==\n\nSocial Income initiative was launched 2019 in [[Zurich]], Switzerland. It started as an initiative by [[Random Institute]] to support artists in need in underdeveloped countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://randominstitute.org/event/social-income|title=Social Income|website=Random Institute|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> In 2020 the initiative was expanded through a residency program offered by the independent foundation Stroom, [[The Hague]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stroom.nl/activiteiten/manifestatie.php?m_id=1788867|title=Our House, your Home \u2013 Stroom|website= Stroom|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\n== Activity ==\nSocial Income is a system of [[wealth redistribution]] in the form of unconditional, long-term cash payments<ref name=ft>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2/a1101f00-e8fd-11e2-aead-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2YrNfbJGn | title =The Undercover Economist: How to give money away |last = Harford|first = Tim|date = July 12, 2013}}</ref> for people in need, paid for by volunteer contributors from across the world. The project's approach to redistribution is taking the enormous income gap between global north and south as a starting point. Currently Social Income's transfers funds to people in need in Sierra Leone.\n\n== Funding ==\nIn contrast to [[Universal Basic Income]], which would be provided by a state or government, Social Income is provided from person to person. Individual contributors pay 1% of their monthly paycheck, which is added to the social income fund and directly deposited to a recipient's mobile phone.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://socialincome.org Social Income website]\n* [https://www.uid.admin.ch/Detail.aspx?uid_id=CHE-289.611.695&lang=en Registration Swiss Government]\n\n[[Category:Poverty-related organizations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox organization\n| name = Social Income\n| logo = Social Income Logo.svg\n| logo_size = 250px\n| type = Alleviating [[poverty]] through [[cash transfers]]\n| founded_date = {{Start date and age|2019}}\n| status = Non-Profit Association \n| registration_id = CHE-289.611.695\n| homepage = {{URL|socialincome.org}}\n| location_city = [[Zurich]]\n| area_served = [[Sierra Leone]]\n}}\n\n'''Social Income''' is a [[non-profit organization|nonprofit organization]] operating in West Africa that helps people living in [[poverty]] by making [[unconditional cash transfer]]s to them via mobile phone. Currently Social Income transfers funds to people in need in [[Sierra Leone]].\n\n== History ==\n\nSocial Income initiative was launched 2019 in [[Zurich]], Switzerland. It started as an initiative by [[Random Institute]] to support artists in need in underdeveloped countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://randominstitute.org/event/social-income|title=Social Income|website=Random Institute|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>. In 2020 the initiative was expanded through a residency program offered by the independent foundation Stroom, [[The Hague]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stroom.nl/activiteiten/manifestatie.php?m_id=1788867|title=Our House, your Home \u2013 Stroom|website= Stroom|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\n== Activity ==\nSocial Income is a system of [[wealth redistribution]] in the form of unconditional, long-term cash payments<ref name=ft>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2/a1101f00-e8fd-11e2-aead-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2YrNfbJGn | title =The Undercover Economist: How to give money away |last = Harford|first = Tim|date = July 12, 2013}}</ref> for people in need, paid for by volunteer contributors from across the world. The project's approach to redistribution is taking the enormous income gap between global north and south as a starting point. Currently Social Income's transfers funds to people in need in Sierra Leone.\n\n== Funding ==\nIn contrast to [[Universal Basic Income]], which would be provided by a state or government, Social Income is provided from person to person. Individual contributors pay 1% of their monthly paycheck, which is added to the social income fund and directly deposited to a recipient's mobile phone.\n\n==External links==\n* [https://socialincome.org Social Income website]\n* [https://www.uid.admin.ch/Detail.aspx?uid_id=CHE-289.611.695&lang=en Registration Swiss Government]\n\n\n\n[[Category:Poverty-related organizations]]\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reflist", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Income"}
